i## sin, cos, tan: Taylor Expansion		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iThe trigonometric functions, sine and cosine, have a relatively easy		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iway to compute: Taylor expansions. We all know that the sine function		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ihas the following Taylor expansion:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iWe can observe that each expanded item can be calculated with basic		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iarithmetric operations. Therefore, we can implement the following		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ifunctions in Nix:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
