iFor the square root function, we can iterate with the famous Newtonian		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
imethod. The iteration formula I'm using is:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iOf which		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iis the input to the square root function.		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iWe can implement Newtonian square root calculation in Nix with the		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
ifollowing code, and iterate until the change in result is below		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
iepsilon:		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  {		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    # Square root function		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    sqrt = x: let		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      helper = tmp: let		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        value = (tmp + 1.0 * x / tmp) / 2;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      in		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        if (fabs (value - tmp)) < epsilon		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        then value		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i        else helper value;		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i    in		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      if x < epsilon		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      then 0		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i      else helper (1.0 * x);		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i  }		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
i		{{server_addr}}	{{server_port}}
